- Web UI will provide rudimentary functionality even without JavaScript support
	- Can download the map in several formats (PNG, PDF)
	- Can display historical version of the map
	- Other things if possible and feasible
	- Immediate/aggregate data view
- At least JavaScript 8 is required (07/2018) for advanced functions
	- Moving objects around
	- Attaching extra information to routers and networks (names, descriptions, TODOs, etc.)
- Push (server to client) notification when the map changes
	- Find an efficient solution for modern clients
	- Long polling as fallback for legacy clients
